data.description: Ideal ranch-style, brick 1950s 2 bed/1.5 bath home in the highly sought-after University Hills neighborhood. This home has had a very detailed makeover, including all-new flooring, paint, baseboard, water heater, kitchen, bathrooms, appliances, windows, plumbing - lighting fixtures, Cabinets and tops!  The sophisticated kitchen includes all new appliances including a convection range! The rear flex room is currently serving as a spacious dining area but could be a larger family room or guest room. The sewer line is being replaced and the roof is under 2 years old.  Enjoy the best of both worlds, a classic BRICK ranch and all the conveniences of new features & design! This property boasts an enviable location, situated just one mile from the I-25 freeway and within walking distance to stores and restaurants, coffee shops, convenience is at your fingertips. But that's not all - this area is also experiencing rapid growth with several new construction homes on the street, which could mean great potential for future investment.  The University Hills neighborhood is one of Denver's premier areas, with an excellent reputation for its top-rated schools.  Plus, with the Willshire Golf Course and Eisenhower Rec Center close by, there's always something to do and explore. The property itself is a true gem, boasting twin Maple trees &  lush tree coverage for plenty of shade and a sprinkler system to ensure effortless yard care and a beautiful green lawn. The east-to-west orientation provides abundant natural light in the morning and pleasant, cool evenings in the backyard - with a covered patio for incredible evening dinners al fresco or a great outdoor party! Additionally, the home features a dedicated laundry room with storage & convenient access to the backyard! Don't let this opportunity pass you by - take the first step toward making University Hills your new home today! The house is wired to accept a generator at the electrical panel.
